<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1293,1425]" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">
The genus comprises at least two closely related although externally easily distinguishable species, which are treated subsequently as a common taxon. Study of recently collected material clearly shows that the fasciate hindwinged and the clear hind-winged specimens represent distinct species. The more detailed description of the cryptic species is given under the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[623,705,1401,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Isoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara">
<emphasis box="[623,705,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="26">I. clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
